ðŸ”¹ STEP 6: The Deployment Script (deploy-swarm.sh)

This script does everything automatically:

Builds images

Pushes to Docker Hub

Creates overlay network

Deploys services in Swarm

You ran:

./deploy-swarm.sh

Internally, it did:

Build backend image

Build frontend image

Push both images to Docker Hub

Create overlay network

Deploy Docker Swarm stack

ðŸ”¹ STEP 7: Verify Deployment
Check services
docker service ls


Expected:

urban_backend   1/1
urban_frontend  1/1
urban_mysql     1/1

Check running containers
docker ps

ðŸ”¹ STEP 8: Access Application
Component	URL
Frontend	http://<SERVER-IP>
Backend API	http://<SERVER-IP>:8081
ðŸ”¹ STEP 9: Scale Services (Optional)
docker service scale urban_backend=2
docker service scale urban_frontend=2


Swarm automatically load-balances traffic.

ðŸ”¹ STEP 10: Stop or Remove Everything
Stop services:
docker stack rm urban

Remove images:
